quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  12,50,"The King said, “Bring him to me.” But when the messenger came to him, he said, “Go back to your master and ask him, ‘What was the case of the women who cut their hands?’ Indeed, my Lord is All-Knowing of their guile.”"
  12,51,"The king said, “What happened when you [O women] tried to seduce Joseph?” They said, “Allah forbid; we know nothing bad about him.” The chief minister’s wife said, “Now the truth has come to light. It was I who tried to seduce him, and he is surely the truthful"
  12,52,"That is because Joseph should know that I did not betray him in his absence, for Allah does not let the guile of the betrayers to succeed.”"
  12,53,"I do not absolve myself of blame. Indeed, the human soul prompts one to evil, except those to whom my Lord may show mercy. Indeed, my Lord is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.”"
  12,54,"The King said, “Bring him to me, so that I will appoint him [as an adviser] exclusively to myself.” Then when he spoke to him, he said, “You are today in a highly esteemed position and fully trusted by us.”"
  12,55,"Joseph said, “Put me in charge of the storehouses of the land; I am indeed a good keeper and knowledgeable.”"
  12,56,"This is how We established Joseph in the land so that he may settle wherever he wished. We extend Our mercy to whom We will, and We do not let the reward of those who do good to be lost"
  12,57,But the reward of the Hereafter is better for those who believe and fear Allah